abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, June 2. -- The strong room of the Oceanic Steamship Company's steamer Alameda, which arrived to-day from Australia and Honolulu, was robbed on the voyage, $25,000 in gold being, missing. While the Alameda was at Sydney thirty boxes, containing 150,000 English sovereigns, were put in the treasure room of the vessel, consigned to San Francisco. In each box were 5,000 sovereigns, and each was duly sealed and labeled.

abstract: HILLSBOROUGH, New Mexico, June 4. -- Capt. abstract: MENOMINEE, Mich., June 9. -- The Menominee and St. Paul Railroad Company was organized to-day with a capital stock of $2,000,000. abstract: SEA CLIFF, L. I., June 11. -- Bishop McConnell of Brooklyn to-day laid the cornerston of St. Boniface's Roman Catholic Church in this village. The new church will have cost $9,000 when completed.

abstract: WASHINGTON, June 14. -- Henry O. Havemeyer, President of the American Sugar Refining Company, was examined by the Industrial Commission to-day in connection with its investigation of trusts. This attack was made in a written statement, which the witness read in a ringing voice.

abstract: NEWPORT, R.I., June 20. -- The big singlestickers Navahoe and Defender this afternoon went outside for a short race. The Navahoe was leaving her anchorage in the inner harbor when the Defender was seen to hoist her big mainsail, a good breeze blowing from the southwest. As the Navahoe sailed past Fort Adams the Defender hoisted her anchor, and her sails quickly filled, and like an arrow she was off.

abstract: A small riot in which three men were badly wounded occurred yesterday morning at McKeon and Varian Streets, Stapleton, S.I.
